{"id": 7281, "title": "Ticket #7281: Exchange a SCITOKEN for a TOKEN", "description": "<blockquote>\nA <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=SciToken\" title=\"Sci Token\">SciToken</a></span> is a bearer token, issued by a third party, that describes allowed capabilities.  Two downsides of this authentication method are:\n\n<p></p><ul>\n<li>In order to utilize it with HTCondor as part of a new security session, the server needs to have a SSL certificate.\n</li><li>The server must download the <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=SciToken\" title=\"Sci Token\">SciToken</a></span> issuer's public keys to verify the token's authenticity; this can potentially fail.\n</li></ul>\n\n<p>TOKEN auth, on the other hand, does not require a host cert and, because the token is issued by HTCondor, doesn't rely on access to a third party.\n\n</p><p>If we allow a <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=SciToken\" title=\"Sci Token\">SciToken</a></span> to be exchanged for an equivalent-or-more-restricted TOKEN, then subsequent security sessions from the client can be established with the more robust TOKEN method.  Further, the token exchange can be combined with the impersonation token in <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"docpending\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7262\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7262'); return false;\" title=\"Provide ability for collector to receive impersonation tokens\">#7262</a></span> to allow the HTCondor-CE to run completely without a host certificate in the following setup:\n\n</p><p></p><ul>\n<li>Sysadmin of HTCondor CE acquires a token allowing the CE to advertise to the OSG collector.\n</li><li>Pilot factory registers its identity with the OSG collector.\n</li><li>Pilot factory uses its identity to obtain an impersonation token as in <span class=\"ticket\"><a class=\"docpending\" href=\"/wiki-archive/tickets/?ticket=7262\" onclick=\"get_ticket_and_populate_wrapper('7262'); return false;\" title=\"Provide ability for collector to receive impersonation tokens\">#7262</a></span>.\n</li><li>Pilot factory contacts the HTCondor-CE, authenticating with its impersonation token, and exchanges the VO's <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=SciToken\" title=\"Sci Token\">SciToken</a></span> for an equivalent TOKEN using the VO's identity at the CE.\n</li><li>Pilot factory creates a new authenticated security session with the remote CE using the VO's TOKEN and can start to submit jobs.\n</li></ul>\n\n<p>Finally, because the HTCondor-CE doesn't need a host certificate for any of its authentication methods, it also doesn't need a public IP or hostname -- the CE itself can (I think) be run behind a NAT.</p></blockquote>", "remarks": "<blockquote>\n<em>2019-Sep-30 12:44:34 by bbockelm:</em> <br/>\n\nAssociated PR: <a class=\"external\" href=\"https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/pull/76\">https://github.com/htcondor/htcondor/pull/76</a>\n\n<p>Should be ready to roll, pending Travis-CI results.\n\n</p><p></p><hr/>\n<em>2020-Aug-27 16:17:49 by tannenba:</em> <br/>\n\nThis ticket was moved for some reason from <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=DocPending\" title=\"Doc Pending\">DocPending</a></span> to Resolved, but there is no documentation... there is just a Version History blurb.  At the very least a new command line tool requires a new man page, yes?  Changing status back to <span class=\"wiki\"><a class=\"missing\" href=\"wiki?p=DocPending\" title=\"Doc Pending\">DocPending</a></span>.</blockquote>", "derived_tickets": "", "attachments": "<html><head></head><body></body></html>", "check_ins": "<table border=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" cellspacing=\"0\">\n<tbody><tr><td align=\"right\" valign=\"top\" width=\"160\">2019-Oct-30 10:06</td>\n<td align=\"center\" valign=\"top\" width=\"30\">\n<span class=\"icon dot\">\u00a0</span></td>\n<td align=\"left\" valign=\"top\"> \nCheck-in <span class=\"chng\"><a href=\"https://git